text: A two-digit number _ab_ is called almost prime if one obtains a two-digit prime number by changing at most one of its digits a and b. (For example, 18 is an almost prime number because 13 is a prime number). is called almost prime if one obtains a two-digit prime number by changing at most one of its digits and (For example, 18 is an almost prime number because 13 is a prime number). == References == Category:Prime numbers Category:Integer sequences
